cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to model the likelihood of contingent event pairs in film scenes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also draws on previous work in common-sense reasoning and causal reasoning, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of unsupervised learning methods and refinement of event pairs using web search counts suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively. Finally, the paper deals with film scene descriptions, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
